    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>Tall, slender elf with copper-brown skin, silver-streaked black hair tied with braided bowstring, and calm green eyes that seem to measure grain and tension in everything he sees. His hands are scarred from forge heat and stained with resin.</em></p><h3>Personality</h3><p>Patient, soft-spoken, and exacting. Faelar speaks as if every word must be carved cleanly before it leaves his mouth. He respects skill over status and distrusts anyone who treats weapons as toys.</p><h3>Motivation</h3><p>Faelar wants to craft one final masterwork bow from moonheart yew, a rare sacred wood from a hidden forest grove now corrupted by undead forces.</p><h3>Mannerisms</h3><p>Runs his thumb along invisible wood grain when thinking. Tests the tension of any string nearby. Pauses before answering, as if listening for wind through leaves. Never hands over a bow without asking what it will be used for.</p><h3>Voice &amp; Accent</h3><p>Quiet, warm, and precise. Old elven cadence with a faint woodland lilt. Rarely raises his voice.</p><h3>Bonds, Ideals, Flaws</h3><ul><li><strong>Bond:</strong> He is bound to the memory of his late mentor, Lethariel Dawnstring. Also feels responsible for protecting the village hunters and younger scouts.</li><li><strong>Ideal:</strong> A weapon should protect life before it takes life. True craftsmanship begins with restraint.</li><li><strong>Flaw:</strong> Carries old guilt over crafting weapons used in a massacre during a border conflict. Slow to trust adventurers.</li></ul><hr><h3>GM Notes</h3><p>Use Faelar as a grounded, emotionally restrained NPC with strong moral weight. His quest leads into a haunted forest encounter, an undead guardian, or a moral choice: cut the branch quickly or cleanse the grove first.</p><h3>Secrets</h3><p>1. Faelar once made a bow for a noble ranger who used it to assassinate civilians during a succession war.\n2. The moonheart yew grove may contain the restless spirit of his former mentor, Lethariel Dawnstring.\n3. One of the three magical arrows he gives the party is experimental and may react unpredictably near undead corruption.</p><h3>Relationships</h3><p>Village hunters: trusted supplier and quiet mentor. Local carpenter: friendly rivalry. Village elder: respects Faelar but worries his obsession with the grove will bring danger. Unknown undead presence: connected to the corruption of the moonheart yew grove.</p><h3>Plot Hooks</h3><p>1. Faelar asks the party to retrieve a living branch of moonheart yew from a hidden grove.\n2. He warns the grove may be guarded by undead or corrupted forest spirits.\n3. The party must decide whether to take the wood by force, cleanse the corruption, or communicate with the grove's guardian.\n4. A hunter returns with a black-veined arrow shaft from the forest, proving the corruption is spreading.</p><h3>Encounter Ideas</h3><p>1. The party follows old elven trail marks that only appear under moonlight.\n2. Undead archers formed from bark, bone, and old leather guard the grove.\n3. A corrupted dryad or elven revenant demands proof that the party will not misuse the sacred wood.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
